This year, the vaccination should cover 219,000 people in the region, including at least 70 percent of all children.
To date, vaccines have been administered to 49 thousand Sakhalin and Kuril residents.
More than 10,000 people have undergone the procedure at the South Sakhalin City Children's Hospital.
Children as young as six months, transportation workers, health-care workers, and those who have more contact with large numbers of people are at greater risk, say health officials.
They can all get a free flu shot.
Also free for people with chronic diseases, pregnant women and students.
