According to him, the scientific center conducts work on supersonic subjects both within the framework of international consortia and cooperation with the Ministry of Industry and Trade.
"We feel it will take us two to three years to get a technology demonstrator, and another 10-15 years to get a production car that can transport across the vastness of our homeland", Sypala added.
He said that now the Russian specialists are faced with the question of how to make the equipment economical and safe at the same time.
In early September, the developer of aviation equipment PJSC "Tupolev" announced the completion of pre-project work on a supersonic passenger aircraft, according to calculations, the aircraft will be able to develop a speed of up to 1900 km / h at an altitude of 11 km.
