The expensive violin was sold to a pawnshop for a pittance .
When a man brought a violin to the LBC Boutique and Loan pawnshop in Somerville, Massachusetts, the pawnshop employee offered only $50 for the apparently old and unpresentable instrument.
But experienced store manager Dylan McDermitt suspected that it was an old and expensive tool, and he sought expert advice.
