"Germans like to plan things quietly, but Russians, as the saying goes, "pull over and drive fast".
But I think it is not important for the understanding between peoples and for the work of the translator", the expert told RIA Novosti.
To understand that the two countries cannot do without each other, the translator says, "it is enough to know history".
